description._content: Catalog #: 09_01649 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Long Beach California Additional Information: Squadron ""B"" with a Thomas-morse O-19C aircraft in Long Beach California, 1935. Harry Haw is standing third from right. Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
